id: pm-2kkl
title: "GH-348/GH-376: Windows nightly Vitest worker fork exits unexpectedly after passing tests"
description: "Windows Nightly Validation has repeatedly hit teardown-only Vitest worker fork exits after all assertions pass: first GH-348 on the retired windows-latest/Node 20 lane, then GH-376 on windows-latest/Node 24 after 255/256 files passed. The active mitigation hardens background test-run signal coverage so tests no longer terminate the Vitest parent worker, keeps MCP upgrade routing coverage dry-run/network-free, and ensures the required Docs and Skills branch-protection check runs on every pull request. Keep this item open until the next full scheduled Nightly Validation confirms the full Windows suite is green."
type: Issue
status: in_progress
priority: 3
tags[5]: "area:ci","area:tests",cross-platform,flake,windows
created_at: "2026-06-23T12:18:09.377Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-26T22:59:03.529Z"
author: claude-code-agent
parent: pm-u9d0
