comments[27]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-23T15:39:40.414Z",codex,"Continuation check (codex): GH-348 still open and remains separate from the SDK version-compatibility branch. Current main CI run 28028252104 had Windows regression (Node 20) green, while GH-348 describes intermittent Nightly Validation worker teardown after tests pass. No SDK version-compat code changes touch the suspected LanceDB/OTLP teardown surface; leave pm-2kkl open for a Windows-runner reproduction/hardening lane."
  "2026-06-24T09:06:44.562Z",codex-gpt5,"Continuation note: GitHub issue #348 was refreshed by run 28083306766 on 2026-06-24 for windows-latest / Node 20. PR #353 / pm-2p7a resolves the live scheduled failure class by removing unsupported Node 20 nightly lanes as part of the Node >=22.18 TypeScript-only extension runtime floor; branch nightly matrix is Node 22/24/25 on Ubuntu plus Node 24 on macOS/Windows. Keep this issue open until PR #353 is merged to main and the next scheduled nightly no longer reports Node 20."
  "2026-06-25T09:18:47.079Z",claude-code-agent,"Root cause located (2026-06-25, via pm-xaib / GH-363). The teardown \"Worker forks emitted error / Worker exited unexpectedly\" is the detached telemetry flush spawn in src/core/telemetry/runtime.ts (scheduleTelemetryFlush) launching a child via spawn() WITHOUT a child.on(\"error\", ...) listener. An asynchronous spawn failure (locked-down Windows runner, EACCES, missing runner) emits an unhandled \"error\" event that Node re-throws as an uncaught exception, crashing the vitest fork worker on teardown. The sibling search background-refresh spawn (src/core/search/background-refresh.ts dispatchRefreshChild) already had exactly this guard — telemetry was the lone outlier. Secondary aggravator: the unit test \"covers non-inline scheduler gate and start failure fallback\" deleted VITEST and launched a REAL, network-touching, untracked node flush child instead of mocking spawn, leaving an orphan process on Windows.\n\nFix shipped in pm-xaib: (1) add child.on(\"error\") gate-release to the telemetry spawn mirroring background-refresh; (2) mock node:child_process in the telemetry test so no real orphan child is spawned; (3) add a focused regression test that emits an async \"error\" and asserts the spawn gate is released; (4) run tests/unit/core/telemetry/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts in the per-PR windows-regression Node 24 job so this class is caught before the nightly. Closing this issue is gated on the Windows nightly turning green after pm-xaib merges.\n"
  "2026-06-25T10:53:16.375Z",claude-code-agent,"Root-cause fix SHIPPED to main in #365 (squash 6f88efcc) via pm-xaib: scheduleTelemetryFlush now attaches a child.on(\"error\") handler that releases the spawn gate, so an asynchronous detached-spawn failure can no longer surface as the unhandled error that crashed the vitest fork worker on teardown. The culprit unit spec (telemetry-runtime.spec.ts) was also switched from launching a real network-touching node flush child to a mocked spawn, and now runs in the per-PR windows-regression (Node 24) job — green on the real windows-latest/Node 24 runner.\n\nRemaining gate to CLOSE: the teardown \"Worker exited unexpectedly\" only manifested in the FULL nightly suite, so final confirmation is the next scheduled Nightly Validation run (windows-latest/Node 24, ~07:50 UTC). If that run is green, close pm-2kkl; the windows-regression isolation pass + the root-cause fix make this highly likely. Keeping open until the nightly confirms (terminal-evidence policy, pm-e9zh).\n"
  "2026-06-26T08:55:50.802Z",codex-gpt5,"Investigation note: GH issue #376 / run 28225122314 failed only on windows-latest Node 24. All 5113 executed tests passed and Vitest failed on one unhandled worker-fork exit after 255/256 files, same terminal symptom as this item after the telemetry spawn guard shipped; inspecting nightly/test-runner surfaces before patching."
  "2026-06-26T10:06:36.227Z",codex-gpt5,"Verification note: real repo coverage passed after the MCP dry-run fix: node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage -> 256 files, 5132 tests, 100/100/100/100 (31815 statements, 24773 branches, 5403 functions, 30538 lines). Do not run full coverage as a linked pm test in schema-sandbox mode: pm test --run seeds package extensions but the sandbox tracker is intentionally empty, causing package runtime tests to fail with tracker_not_initialized. Focused linked tests remain sandbox-safe."
  "2026-06-26T10:10:51.818Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation evidence: hardened tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts so background-run signal coverage uses process.emit from the test process after worker progress is observed instead of child process.kill(process.ppid, SIGTERM/SIGINT), avoiding Windows Vitest fork self-termination. Added that spec to the required Windows regression slice in .github/workflows/ci.yml. Kept MCP dynamic package upgrade routing test dry-run only so coverage is network-free and stable. Verification passed: pm test pm-2kkl --run --progress (3/3 linked tests), node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (256 files, 5132 tests, 100/100/100/100), pnpm typecheck, pnpm quality:static, git diff --check, pnpm contracts:check, pm health --check-only --summary --json, pnpm audit --audit-level low, pnpm changelog:pm:check with pm-changelog 2026.6.20, node dist/cli.js package doctor --project --detail deep --json, pnpm security:scan, Sentry/telemetry gate ok (0 critical/high Sentry, telemetry finish error rate 0.74%). Manual temp smoke passed in /tmp/tmp.ogpaLWgnKJ using isolated PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH and dist/cli.js: init, create, claim, update, comment, linked test, health, validate, close, release."
  "2026-06-26T10:17:24.015Z",codex-gpt5,"Release gate evidence: pnpm release:gates passed after this change. It rebuilt the CLI, passed typecheck/static/docs gates, coverage 100/100/100/100, version policy, security scan, packed npx smoke (packages=11), and package-first dogfood (88 commands, linked test run passed). Semantic dogfood was skipped by design because PM_DOGFOOD_SEMANTIC was not set."
  "2026-06-26T10:18:23.928Z",codex-gpt5,"PR evidence: opened GitHub PR #377 (Fix Windows background test-run signal coverage) for this implementation and requested review agents on the PR."
  "2026-06-26T10:25:03.335Z",codex-gpt5,"Review response: addressed Gemini feedback on PR #377 by removing the remaining fixed 50ms signal timer and extending progress polling to 10 seconds in the background signal tests. Re-verified focused test-runs-command spec and the full Windows regression slice locally."
  "2026-06-26T10:26:23.786Z",codex-gpt5,"PR review loop: pushed follow-up commit 2c69fcf0 to PR #377 addressing Gemini timing-race feedback and re-requested review agents on the new head."
  "2026-06-26T10:35:11.158Z",codex-gpt5,"Review response: addressed current Gemini feedback on PR #377 by replacing process.emit-based signal simulation with captured process.on SIGTERM/SIGINT handlers in the worker signal tests, avoiding Vitest global signal listeners entirely. Re-verified focused background-run spec, Windows regression slice, and pnpm typecheck locally."
  "2026-06-26T10:44:30.606Z",codex-gpt5,"Review response: addressed latest Gemini feedback on PR #377 by adding workerFinished guards to the signal readiness polling loops so early worker failure/exit cannot add a 10 second wait. Re-verified focused background-run spec, Windows regression slice, and pnpm typecheck locally."
  "2026-06-26T10:52:55.839Z",codex-gpt5,"Review response: addressed latest Gemini feedback on PR #377 by delegating non-SIGTERM/SIGINT process.on/off calls to the original process methods while still capturing worker signal handlers. Re-verified focused background-run spec, Windows regression slice, and pnpm typecheck locally."
  "2026-06-26T11:03:20.687Z",codex-gpt5,"Review follow-up: mocked process.addListener/removeListener aliases in both background signal tests so future listener-registration changes still exercise the same SIGTERM/SIGINT capture path. Verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts passed 28 tests; PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/cli/cli-main-errors.spec.ts tests/unit/core/schema/runtime-schema-path-win32-guard.spec.ts tests/unit/helpers/scriptModule.spec.ts tests/unit/scripts/ tests/unit/packages/runtime-loaders.spec.ts tests/unit/core/telemetry/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts passed 35 files / 649 tests; pnpm typecheck passed; git diff --check passed."
  "2026-06-26T11:12:35.281Z",codex-gpt5,"Review follow-up: addressed current Gemini feedback on PR #377 by storing captured SIGTERM/SIGINT listeners in arrays and honoring targeted removals, so the signal mocks no longer overwrite earlier handlers if multiple listeners are registered. Verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts passed 28 tests; PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/cli/cli-main-errors.spec.ts tests/unit/core/schema/runtime-schema-path-win32-guard.spec.ts tests/unit/helpers/scriptModule.spec.ts tests/unit/scripts/ tests/unit/packages/runtime-loaders.spec.ts tests/unit/core/telemetry/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts passed 35 files / 649 tests; pnpm typecheck passed; git diff --check passed."
  "2026-06-26T11:22:18.146Z",codex-gpt5,"Review follow-up: addressed current Gemini feedback on PR #377 by removing redundant addListener/removeListener signal mocks after confirming production background-run code uses process.on/off, and by catching signal-readiness cleanup errors in finally so cleanup cannot mask the worker result. Verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts passed 28 tests; PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/cli/cli-main-errors.spec.ts tests/unit/core/schema/runtime-schema-path-win32-guard.spec.ts tests/unit/helpers/scriptModule.spec.ts tests/unit/scripts/ tests/unit/packages/runtime-loaders.spec.ts tests/unit/core/telemetry/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts passed 35 files / 649 tests; pnpm typecheck passed; git diff --check passed."
  "2026-06-26T11:31:52.981Z",codex-gpt5,"Review follow-up: addressed current Gemini and CodeRabbit feedback on PR #377 by gating manual SIGTERM/SIGINT handler invocation on observed stderr progress and an active worker, so timeout or early-finish paths no longer invoke captured handlers unconditionally. Verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts passed 28 tests; PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/cli/cli-main-errors.spec.ts tests/unit/core/schema/runtime-schema-path-win32-guard.spec.ts tests/unit/helpers/scriptModule.spec.ts tests/unit/scripts/ tests/unit/packages/runtime-loaders.spec.ts tests/unit/core/telemetry/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts passed 35 files / 649 tests; pnpm typecheck passed; git diff --check passed."
  "2026-06-26T11:41:43.221Z",codex-gpt5,"Review follow-up: addressed current Gemini feedback on PR #377 by delegating uncaptured SIGTERM/SIGINT process.off listeners back to the original process.off implementation while still removing handlers captured by the test mock locally. Verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts passed 28 tests; PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/cli/cli-main-errors.spec.ts tests/unit/core/schema/runtime-schema-path-win32-guard.spec.ts tests/unit/helpers/scriptModule.spec.ts tests/unit/scripts/ tests/unit/packages/runtime-loaders.spec.ts tests/unit/core/telemetry/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts passed 35 files / 649 tests; pnpm typecheck passed; git diff --check passed."
  "2026-06-26T11:51:26.582Z",codex-gpt5,"Review follow-up: addressed current Gemini feedback on PR #377 by extracting the repeated process.on/off signal-capture mock setup into a typed captureProcessSignalHandlers helper used by both background signal tests. Verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts passed 28 tests; PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/cli/cli-main-errors.spec.ts tests/unit/core/schema/runtime-schema-path-win32-guard.spec.ts tests/unit/helpers/scriptModule.spec.ts tests/unit/scripts/ tests/unit/packages/runtime-loaders.spec.ts tests/unit/core/telemetry/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts passed 35 files / 649 tests; pnpm typecheck passed; git diff --check passed."
  "2026-06-26T12:00:41.469Z",codex-gpt5,"Review follow-up: addressed current Gemini feedback on PR #377 by attaching catch handlers directly to the signal readiness IIFE promises and awaiting the already-handled promises in finally, eliminating the unhandled-rejection window. Verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts passed 28 tests; PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/cli/cli-main-errors.spec.ts tests/unit/core/schema/runtime-schema-path-win32-guard.spec.ts tests/unit/helpers/scriptModule.spec.ts tests/unit/scripts/ tests/unit/packages/runtime-loaders.spec.ts tests/unit/core/telemetry/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts passed 35 files / 649 tests; pnpm typecheck passed; git diff --check passed."
  "2026-06-26T12:10:11.984Z",codex-gpt5,"Review follow-up: addressed current Gemini feedback on PR #377 by adding process.addListener/removeListener alias support inside the shared captureProcessSignalHandlers helper, keeping alias and primary process listener APIs consistent without duplicating test setup. Verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts passed 28 tests; PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/cli/cli-main-errors.spec.ts tests/unit/core/schema/runtime-schema-path-win32-guard.spec.ts tests/unit/helpers/scriptModule.spec.ts tests/unit/scripts/ tests/unit/packages/runtime-loaders.spec.ts tests/unit/core/telemetry/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts passed 35 files / 649 tests; pnpm typecheck passed; git diff --check passed."
  "2026-06-26T12:25:16.629Z",codex-gpt5,"Branch-protection follow-up: PR #377 could not merge because main requires the Docs and Skills check but docs.yml skipped non-doc pull requests via path filters. Updated .github/workflows/docs.yml so pull_request always runs while keeping push-to-main path filters. Verification passed: pnpm quality:docs-skills; pnpm quality:docs-links; git diff --check; pm test pm-2kkl --run --progress passed 5/5 linked checks."
  "2026-06-26T12:36:20.391Z",codex-gpt5,"Review follow-up: addressed current Gemini and CodeRabbit feedback on PR #377 by consolidating process.off fallback handling, extracting shared progress-marker signal dispatch for the two background signal tests, and refreshing the canonical pm title/description/body to reflect the GH-348/GH-376 lineage plus the Docs and Skills branch-protection fix. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts; PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/cli/cli-main-errors.spec.ts tests/unit/core/schema/runtime-schema-path-win32-guard.spec.ts tests/unit/helpers/scriptModule.spec.ts tests/unit/scripts/ tests/unit/packages/runtime-loaders.spec.ts tests/unit/core/telemetry/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts; pnpm typecheck; git diff --check; pm test pm-2kkl --run --progress passed 5/5 linked checks."
  "2026-06-26T12:46:58.577Z",codex-gpt5,"Review follow-up: addressed current Gemini feedback on PR #377 by changing the signal-stop fixture interval to clear itself after SIGTERM, so the child exits cleanly instead of relying on the short force-kill delay. The other open Gemini offSpy fallback thread is already satisfied by the current single-fallback implementation. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts; PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/cli/cli-main-errors.spec.ts tests/unit/core/schema/runtime-schema-path-win32-guard.spec.ts tests/unit/helpers/scriptModule.spec.ts tests/unit/scripts/ tests/unit/packages/runtime-loaders.spec.ts tests/unit/core/telemetry/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts; pnpm typecheck; git diff --check; pm test pm-2kkl --run --progress passed 5/5 linked checks."
  "2026-06-26T22:24:04.895Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #383 Windows regression follow-up: GitHub run 28268311966 failed the Windows regression job on tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts with EPERM during writeFileAtomic rename of a background test-run record. Reused this existing Windows lineage and patched src/core/fs/fs-utils.ts with bounded Windows EPERM/EBUSY rename retries. Verification so far: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/core/fs/fs-utils.spec.ts passed 7 tests; PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 Windows regression slice command passed 35 files / 649 tests locally."
  "2026-06-26T22:40:18.064Z",codex-gpt5,"Evidence: implemented Windows atomic write retry hardening for transient EPERM/EBUSY rename failures in src/core/fs/fs-utils.ts and added focused branch coverage in tests/unit/core/fs/fs-utils.spec.ts. Verification passed: PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/core/fs/fs-utils.spec.ts (9 tests); pm test pm-2kkl --run --progress (6 linked tests passed); pnpm typecheck; pnpm lint; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate; pnpm security:scan; npm pack --dry-run --silent; pnpm changelog:pm:check unchanged with pm-changelog 2026.6.20; pm health --check-only --summary --json ok with 0 warnings; pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift --json ok with known validate_resolution_missing_fields:258 warning and history_drift ok; git diff --check; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 256 files / 5136 tests with 100/100/100/100 coverage. Manual temp-dir smoke from this PR remained valid for CodeFactor parity tooling; this update specifically fixes PR #383 Windows regression run 28268311966 job 83760159340."
