body: "## Current scope 2026-06-26\n\nThis item tracks the Windows nightly teardown symptom across GH-348 and GH-376: Vitest reports all assertions passing, then a worker fork exits unexpectedly during teardown on the Windows runner. The Node 20 lane has already been retired by the Node >=22.18 runtime floor; the current failing signal is GH-376 on windows-latest / Node 24 after 255 of 256 files executed successfully.\n\nImplemented in PR #377:\n1. Hardened background test-run signal tests so they capture process SIGTERM/SIGINT handlers and invoke them after worker progress is observed, instead of sending real signals that can terminate the Vitest worker.\n2. Added tests/unit/commands/test-runs-command.spec.ts to the required Windows regression slice.\n3. Kept the MCP dynamic package upgrade action test dry-run only so coverage remains network-free.\n4. Fixed .github/workflows/docs.yml so the required Docs and Skills check is emitted on every pull_request while preserving path filters for push-to-main runs.\n\nVerification recorded on this item includes linked tests, local coverage at 100/100/100/100, release gates, security/audit/changelog checks, Sentry/telemetry gate, and an isolated temp-directory manual pm smoke. Closure remains gated on a full scheduled Nightly Validation run confirming windows-latest / Node 24 no longer reports the teardown worker exit."
